title.narrative: Agree on TOR and carry out pilot for social accountability for Chile Solidario System
Surveys for impact evaluation carried out, including module in 2003 CASEN and 2004 panel survey. Second round of survey is now starting fieldwork. Questionnaire include perception questions.

actual.value: Work continuing on evaluations of parental education.

comment.narrative: Additional work in progress on impact evaluation, focusing on the area of female employment with trust fund resources.

title.narrative: As of October 2007, 262,000 families invited to enter Chile Solidario, of which 249,245 have decided to participate in the Program.

target.value: No target set because entrances could vary depending on poverty trends and macroeconomic conditions.

actual.value: Updated information for 2012 not available yet. Target was to register 50,000 additional families during the year.

title.narrative: Databases relevant to Chile Solidario integrated into the national social protection information system

target.value: 30 Institutions have signed agreements to exchange information.

actual.value: Data bases related to taxes are now being integrated, as well as school attendance information, and property rolls (cars)

comment.narrative: In work to design ingreso etico, additional data bases are likely to be integrated.

title.narrative: Program evaluations completed for 4 programs. Studies for 4 additional programs are in process.
CAS en linea rolled out and training completed.

comment.narrative: Work to undertake reforms of the ficha de Proteccion Social is in progress.
